posts.subject: Fix image post on Tor
posts.body:
Go in about:config
Type "fingerprint"
Deactivate: 

- privacy.resistFingerprinting
- privacy.resistFingerprinting.autoDeclineNoUserInputCanvasPrompts
- services.sync.prefs.sync.privacy.resistFingerprinting

Means you don't need to create an identity on zites such as ZeroID. Basically you aren't forced to have a username and can just use a shared certificate. I checked and you can't even use your own cert if you wanted to, on this Zite. Weird considering Millchan allows it, dunno why 08 was configured that way.
It's obvious they don't run it but why would they not recommend using it ? It's a good solution.

Go in about:config
Type "fingerprint"
Deactivate:
- privacy.resistFingerprinting
- privacy.resistFingerprinting.autoDeclineNoUserInputCanvasPrompts
- services.sync.prefs.sync.privacy.resistFingerprinting

>Image uploading via TOR is currently broken Fixed. You can change the following options to post images via TOR Browser:

>Go in about:config
>Type "fingerprint"
>Deactivate:
>privacy.resistFingerprinting
>privacy.resistFingerprinting.autoDeclineNoUserInputCanvasPrompts
>services.sync.prefs.sync.privacy.resistFingerprinting

Happy to see my fix is used.

>>86b94e60-bdae-4734-aeed-5cee253b9c8b

What does it change ? In most modern countries there are low against file encryption meaning you'll go to jail anyways...
